sshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"nl":{"Abt 1295–17 Oct 1346":"circa 1295–17 oktober 1346","1295–1346":"1295–1346","1300–Male":"1300–Overleden","1310–1357":"1310–1357","1312–Male":"1312–Overleden","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1322–Female":"1322–Overleden","1325–Female":"1325–Overleden","1330–Male":"1330–Overleden","1276–1340":"1276–1340","1276–Female":"1276–Overleden","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1380":"1380","Abt 1295":"circa 1295","1325":"1325","17 Oct 1346":"17 oktober 1346","1357":"1357","1346":"1346","1312":"1312","1322":"1322","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1276":"1276","1320":"1320","Closeburn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Closeburn, Dumfriesshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England"},"en":{"Abt 1295–17 Oct 1346":"about 1295–17 October 1346","1295–1346":"1295–1346","1300–Male":"1300–Deceased","1310–1357":"1310–1357","1312–Male":"1312–Deceased","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1322–Female":"1322–Deceased","1325–Female":"1325–Deceased","1330–Male":"1330–Deceased","1276–1340":"1276–1340","1276–Female":"1276–Deceased","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1380":"1380","Abt 1295":"about 1295","1325":"1325","17 Oct 1346":"17 October 1346","1357":"1357","1346":"1346","1312":"1312","1322":"1322","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1276":"1276","1320":"1320","Closeburn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Closeburn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kirkpatrick","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from either of two places in Dumfriess called Kirkpatrick or any of various other places in Scotland, all so named from the dedication of their church to Saint Patrick. The Scottish word <i>kirk</i> sometimes replaced Gaelic <i>cill</i> ‘church’ in placenames; compare   Kilpatrick  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kilpatrick","meanings":["Irish (Ulster): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Giolla Phádraig</b> ‘son of the servant of (Saint) Patrick’ (Irish <i>Pádraig</i>). See also   Fitzpatrick  .","Scottish: habitational name from any of various places called in Gaelic as <i>cill Padraig</i> ‘church of (Saint) Patrick’. See also   Kirkpatrick  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas Kirkpatrick of Closeburn and Bridburgh was born about 1295, in Closeburn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Roger Kirkpatrick, was 20 and his mother, Kirkpatrick, was 21. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. He died on 17 October 1346, at the age of 52."},"et":{"Abt 1295–17 Oct 1346":"umbes 1295–17. oktoober 1346","1295–1346":"1295–1346","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1310–1357":"1310–1357","1312–Male":"1312–Surnud","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1322–Female":"1322–Surnud","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1276–1340":"1276–1340","1276–Female":"1276–Surnud","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1380":"1380","Abt 1295":"umbes 1295","1325":"1325","17 Oct 1346":"17. oktoober 1346","1357":"1357","1346":"1346","1312":"1312","1322":"1322","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1276":"1276","1320":"1320","Closeburn, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Closeburn, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"Abt 1295–17 Oct 1346":"noin 1295–17. lokakuuta 1346","1295–1346":"1295–1346","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1310–1357":"1310–1357","1312–Male":"1312–Kuollut","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1322–Female":"1322–Kuollut","1325–Female":"1325–Ku